<h3>Malabar Spinach</h3>
<p>"Malabar" can refer to several things, including a plant (Malabar nut/Adhatoda vasica, Malabar spinach/Basella alba, or Malabar chestnut), and each has different uses, ranging from medicinal to culinary and ornamental.<br><span style="color:red">Medicinal Uses:</span>Used to treat tuberculosis, skin diseases, dysentery, diarrhea, and vomiting<br>Powdered leaves are used to treat malaria in southern India.<br>Juice from the leaves can be used to treat diarrhea, dysentery, and control bleeding.<br>The leaves are a good source of vitamins A, B, and C, as well as iron and calcium. </p>
